{{/* User-prompt template for the extraction step. The system prompt
   (chatExtractionSystemPrompt in chat/prompt.go) sets the schema and
   rules; this template provides the inputs.

   Variables:
     .Questions — []QuestionView{ID, Prompt}
     .Goals     — []GoalView{ID, Title, CheckInQuestion}
     .Messages  — []TranscriptLine{Role, Content}
*/ -}}

# Questions on file

{{range .Questions -}}
({{.ID}}) {{.Prompt}}
{{end}}

{{if .Goals -}}
# Active goals on file

Each has a yes/no check-in question. Populate `goal_check_ins` only when
the transcript clearly resolves the question for today. Use the goal_id
verbatim — never invent.

{{range .Goals -}}
({{.ID}}) "{{.CheckInQuestion}}" (goal: {{.Title}})
{{end}}
{{end -}}
# Transcript (verbatim)

{{range .Messages -}}
[{{.Role}}] {{.Content}}

{{end}}

Now emit the JSON object exactly per the schema in the system prompt.
Omit `answers` keys for any question the user did not substantively
answer. Omit goals from `goal_check_ins` unless the user clearly said
yes or no for today. Use the user's voice, never the assistant's.
